#week-title("Two", "Three Years of Inner Practice: A Complete Review")

=== Core Teaching

Month 9 is the integration month. This week, the student reviews the complete
arc of inner practice across all three years — not to summarise or catalogue it,
but to perceive it as a whole. The inner work across three years has included:

- *Year One:* Third Eye Focus; Threefold Breath; Inner Flame; Daily Vigil of
  Nature; Declaration of Intent; the Desoille Descent (DES-1); EFT; the
  elemental meditations; Tarot journal and daily card draw; nature vigils;
  pathwork with Major Arcana cards.
- *Year Two:* Dew collection vigils; receptivity meditations; polar tension
  contemplation; constitutional self-mapping; Tree of Life personal diagram;
  body-awareness practice; the Threefold Breath at depth; somatic awareness;
  the sustained practice commitment; metal meditations; the Adept's Covenant.
- *Year Three:* DES-2 analytical descent; triple point audit; ego-mortality
  contemplation; Binah–Tiphereth arc contemplation; pathworking on the Tree;
  the seasonal audit; extended vigil.

*What the review looks for.* The practitioner who reads their inner work journal
from beginning to end across three years looks for:

1. *Genuine development* — practices that have become more settled, more subtle,
   more naturally present than they were at the beginning.
2. *Unresolved material* — themes that have recurred in the inner work across
   all three years without reaching resolution or integration.
3. *The still centre* — the quality of awareness that has remained constant
   beneath all the changes in technique and content. This is the practitioner's
   own Salt: the fixed, essential character that has been present throughout.

The review is not a celebration of what has been accomplished — it is an honest
perception of what three years of genuine practice has actually done. The
practitioner who can perceive this honestly has the most important instrument
for the Work that lies ahead.

=== Topics This Week

- Reviewing the complete inner practice arc across three years
- What to look for: genuine development, unresolved material, the still centre
- The inner work journal as the primary document for this review
- Writing the three-year inner work synthesis

#inner-work[
  *The Three-Year Inner Work Synthesis*

  After reviewing the complete inner work journal, write a one-to-two page
  synthesis: What has genuinely developed? What has not moved? What is the
  still centre — the quality of awareness that was present in Year One and is
  still present, deepened but not essentially changed?

  This synthesis is the inner work equivalent of the Salt of three years. It
  belongs alongside the Adept's Covenant and the post-curriculum declaration
  as one of the most important documents in the entire journal.
]

